        <p>Use the GDP dataset, already:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Renamed to <strong>gdp</strong></li>
            <li>Converted from <strong>wide ‚Üí long</strong></li>
            <li>Variables include: <code>geo</code>, <code>country</code>, <code>year</code>, <code>gdp</code></li>
        </ul>
        <p>Source: <a href="https://www.gapminder.org/data/" target="_blank">Gapminder GDP per capita</a></p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>‚≠ê What New Columns Can Be Created from the GDP Dataset?</h2>
        <p>Here are highly useful, realistic, and development-focused calculated columns you can add:</p>

        <h3>1Ô∏è‚É£ GDP Category (Low / Middle / High Income)</h3>
        <pre><code>GDP Category =
IF(gdp[gdp] &lt; 2000, "Low Income",
    IF(gdp[gdp] &lt; 10000, "Middle Income", "High Income")
)</code></pre>

        <h3>2Ô∏è‚É£ Decade Column</h3>
        <pre><code>Decade =
INT(gdp[year] / 10) * 10</code></pre>

        <h3>3Ô∏è‚É£ Century Column</h3>
        <pre><code>Century =
"Century " &amp; INT(gdp[year] / 100) + 1</code></pre>

        <h3>4Ô∏è‚É£ Country Initials</h3>
        <pre><code>Country Initials =
CONCATENATE(LEFT(gdp[country],1), RIGHT(gdp[country],1))</code></pre>

        <h3>5Ô∏è‚É£ GDP Rounded (for cleaner visuals)</h3>
        <pre><code>GDP Rounded =
ROUND(gdp[gdp],0)</code></pre>

        <h3>6Ô∏è‚É£ GDP in Thousands (K)</h3>
        <pre><code>GDP (K) =
gdp[gdp] / 1000</code></pre>

        <h3>7Ô∏è‚É£ GDP in Millions (M)</h3>
        <pre><code>GDP (M) =
gdp[gdp] / 1000000</code></pre>

        <h3>8Ô∏è‚É£ Previous Year GDP (Column Version)</h3>
        <pre><code>Previous Year GDP =
CALCULATE(
    SUM(gdp[gdp]),
    FILTER(gdp, gdp[country] = EARLIER(gdp[country]) 
           &amp;&amp; gdp[year] = EARLIER(gdp[year]) - 1)
)</code></pre>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>üìù Key Tasks for December 2</h2>

